==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calendula
<hw>Ca*len"du*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>calendae</ets> calends.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
composite herbaceous plants. One species, <spn>Calendula
officinalis</spn>, is the common marigold, and was supposed to blossom
on the calends of every month, whence the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calendulin</ent>⟦br⟧
